19 Sec. 4. Office of State Fire Marshal to update standards in accordance with
20 National Fire Protection Association standards update. The Department of Public
21 Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal shall update the state-adopted National Fire
22 Protection Association standards by adopting the 2025 edition of the National Fire
23 Protection Association 72: National Fire Alarm and Signaling Code.
24 Sec. 5. Office of State Fire Marshal to convene residential fire sprinklers
25 working group. The Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal shall
26 convene a working group, referred to in this resolve as "the working group," to study the
27 housing and life safety impacts of residential fire sprinklers and explore ways to lower the
28 costs associated with the requirement that construction of residential housing include fire
29 sprinkler systems.
30 1. The State Fire Marshal or the State Fire Marshal's designee shall invite the
31 participation in the working group of the following persons: a representative from the fire
32 sprinkler industry; a municipal fire safety officer; a representative from the housing
33 development industry; and any additional persons considered necessary by the State Fire
34 Marshal to ensure comprehensive stakeholder representation.
35 2. The working group shall:
36 A. Conduct a comprehensive review of the existing sprinkler system requirements for
37 residential buildings with 3 or more units and the affiliated costs of the sprinkler
38 systems;
39 B. Collect and analyze data on the housing and life safety impacts of residential fire
40 sprinkler systems, including, but not limited to, the frequency of the presence of
41 sprinkler systems in reported house fires and the estimated impact on financial loss and
42 life safety impact;
