1 C. Explore innovative incentives to reduce the associated costs of installing sprinkler
2 systems in residential construction; and
3 D. Develop recommendations for legislative and regulatory changes to reduce the
4 costs of installing required residential sprinkler systems.
5 3. The Office of the State Fire Marshal shall provide staff assistance to the working
6 group.
7 4. By January 15, 2027, the Office of the State Fire Marshal shall submit a report on
8 the working group's findings and recommendations, including proposed legislation, to the
9 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing matters. The
10 joint standing committee is authorized to submit legislation based on the report to the 133rd
11 Legislature in 2027.
12 Sec. 6. Department of Professional and Financial Regulation, Office of
