14 than January 15, 2027, the Director of the Office of Professional and Occupational
15 Regulation within the Department of Professional and Financial Regulation shall report to
16 the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing matters
17 regarding the status of the adoption of rules for the elevator and tramway safety program
18 within the Office of Professional and Occupational Regulation pursuant to the Maine
19 Revised Statutes, Title 32, section 15205-A, subsection 2. The committee is authorized to
20 report out legislation related to the report required by this section to the 133rd Legislature
21 in 2027.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This bill is reported out by the Joint Standing Committee on Housing and Economic
2244 Development pursuant to Resolve 2025, chapter 64 to implement the recommendations of
2255 the working group to address regulatory barriers to housing construction. The bill directs:
26 1. The Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal to update state
27 standards to comply with the 2025 edition of the National Fire Protection Association 72:
28 National Fire Alarm and Signaling Code;
29 2. The Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal to convene a
30 working group to study the housing and life safety impacts of residential fire sprinklers and
31 explore ways to lower associated costs and to submit a report on the stakeholder group's
32 findings and recommendations, including proposed legislation, to the joint standing
33 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing matters;
34 3. The Director of the Office of Professional and Occupational Regulation within the
35 Department of Professional and Financial Regulation to report by January 15, 2027 to the
36 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing matters on the
37 status of the adoption of rules for the elevator and tramway safety program.
38 The bill also excludes from the Maine Uniform Building and Energy Code the 2021
39 edition of International Building Code requirements that elevators must have a 2-way
40 communication system and smoke partitions.
